# Omega-Genesis Protocol v12.1

## Compressed Odd Dynamics and a Structural Proof of the Collatz Conjecture

**Author:** Timothy J. Dillon  
**Organization:** 206 Innovation Inc.  
**Version:** v12.1  
**Manuscript:** [Omega_Genesis_v12_1.pdf](https://github.com/206Innovation/OmegaGenesis/Omega_Genesis_v12_1.pdf)

---

## Overview

Omega-Genesis v12.1 presents a structural reduction framework for the Collatz conjecture using the compressed odd map

\[
U(n)=\frac{3n+1}{2^{v_2(3n+1)}}
\]

The manuscript develops a reduction-and-closure architecture built on:

- exact entropic persistence,
- deep-block contraction,
- segment-model exclusion,
- shallow-fragmentation control,
- deep-return dominance,
- finite near-critical reduction,
- and final residual-family elimination.

The central claim of the manuscript is that every positive odd orbit under the compressed odd Collatz map reaches 1, and therefore every positive integer reaches the classical Collatz cycle \{1, 2, 4\}.

---

## What Is New in v12.1

This version strengthens the manuscript into a more referee-facing form by:

- tightening the theorem spine,
- rewriting Sections 4–7 with explicit reduction logic,
- upgrading the near-critical endgame in Section 8,
- strengthening Sections 9.6–9.7,
- clarifying the admissible-core graph argument,
- and separating the computational appendix from the logical proof structure.

Key improvements include:

- explicit theorem-controlled endgame constants,
- a formal obstruction-completeness chain,
- a cleaner cycle-to-template bridge,
- and a stronger final closure sequence.

